HEADWORD: Omniscience
<hw>Om*nis"cience</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>omniscience</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
omniscient; the quality of knowing everything; -- an attribute peculiar
to God.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
